cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC. 

This paper deals with query answering in the presence of ontologies, which is a topic closely related to databases (cs.DB). The use of OWL 2 QL ontologies also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of query answering, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The study of tree-like queries and treewidth is related to graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), while the analysis of rewritings and tractability results involves logic and formal languages (cs.LO).
